Name: Peaches
Weight: 40 pounds
Age: 9 years
Gender: female
Breed: boxer mix
Colour: red and white

Good with adults:  yes
Good with kids: older ones 
Good with other dogs: no, should be the only dog in the home
Good with cats:  no
House trained: working on it
Crate trained: yes and travels well in crate
Energy level:  medium
Can be handled/touched:  yes
Barker: at times to get attention (not excessive)
Flight risk:  not typically 
Food aggressive:  no
Walks on leash:  yes
Leash reactive with other dogs: yes
Rides well in car:  yes
Destructive:  not typically 
Needs a home with a yard: no
Needs a home with another dog: Needs to be an only dog
Can live in an apartment:  yes, but would do better in a home

Peaches probably led a hard life before she was rescued.
She was severely malnourished due to overbreeding and neglect, weighing only 34 pounds. It took weeks of healthy food (and treatment of intestinal parasites) for her to reach her current body weight of about 40 pounds, she still needs to be on another 7-10lbs. Anxious at first, she was intolerant of almost all other dogs. During her stay at SSAR, Peaches has had the opportunity to meet dogs of different breeds and temperaments. She can now have supervised play with her rescue buddy, Diesel, whose goal in life is to have fun! She enjoys the company of people, and off leash she mostly just wants to stick by your side.?
As her confidence has grown, Peaches continues to show her attraction to humans. She does well on a leash and is beginning to learn commands, particularly when not distracted by other dogs. She is a sweet and loving girl and deserves to know a loving home for the first time in her life.

animal.description: Meet Lyla, we had to take action in less than 48 hours to help this sweet girl.  Lyla is a 13-year-old black beauty whose life took an unexpected turn. As many older labs she has some arthritis in her legs plus some nerve damage in one foot. Her legs are not as strong as they once were. Her family has recently moved north and decided the cold would not be good for her arthritis. In addition, the living accommodations they chose have stairs and Lyla is not able to climb stairs on her own so they contacted us. Lyla weighs 60 pounds and her only issue appears to be some small fatty tumors and the weakness in her legs, she has had a recent checkup which confirms this as well. She is alert, LOVES food but needs to be careful to keep her lean so she is better able to get around. Lyla has a good routine, she asks to go to the bathroom, but you will need to remind her as she settles into a new surrounding and learns her way around. Lyla is pretty and so sweet; she loves people and loves to follow her person around the house. She enjoys going outside and is good on a leash, but the walks need to be short and on grass. Her pads are very soft and because of the nerve issue, concrete may injure her paw. She can maneuver indoor floor surfaces very well. Lyla is a good car rider and will greet every morning with a happy bounce!  Lyla will need a family on the quiet side. She is good with kids and other dogs but she is not really sturdy enough on her feet to be in a home with younger dogs or younger children. Lyla will need a parent that is home much of the time, although she is well house trained and will generally nap while you are gone. Lyla would be excellent companion to a retired individual that lives is a rancher with no stairs and a fenced in yard.   Lyla needs a patient dog loving parent that understands the joys of caring for an older dog. Her vision sees pretty good and her hearing seems to be okay at different octaves. Her sense of smell remains very keen. She will need parents that will take care of her changing physical needs, currently she is on Cosequin and she would benefit from water therapy to keep her legs strong.  She desires, parents that will spend time with her, love on her, work on mental and environmental stimulation, and feed her appropriately. She is a happy lab but just cannot wiggle like she used to. She needs one story living with no step access to a grassy outside area.  Lyla does not bark or really make any sounds; she needs someone alert she stands at the door to go out. Lyla is spayed and will be microchipped and up to date on vaccinations prior to adoption. Lyla is a proud dog, who will enhance your life and needs love and support for the rest of her life. Please consider Lyla.  Sponsorship towards the adoption fee is available to the right home. To be considered please complete our online pre-adoption application. http://www.southernskiesrescue.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Deac is a 6 year old Harlequin Great Dane who doesn't let his age slow him down. Deac has high energy for a Dane of his age but at times has trouble going up stairs and just needs to take it slow doing so. Deac gets along well with other dogs but will bark at every dog he sees due to over excitement. Aside from the barking, he is very good on leash. He will stay fairly close to you whenever he is on a walk. He is also very gentle with everyone he needs. Whenever he meets someone for the first time, they instantly fall in love with his loving nature. Loud noises don't seem to bother him but he is very attentive to every noise. Getting baths isn't a problem for Deac, as long as the water stays off his head and loves getting dried off afterwards with a towel. As most Danes love being next to their humans and want nothing but to be loved. Deac is no different. Whether it's going for a little walk or laying on the couch, Deac is happy with either. The more you love him, the more he will love you back. Deac is a very gentle dog who is looking for his furever home.

Update Nov 18
Deac is still an older dog but trapped inside of a younger dog's body. Despite being 6, you would never be able to tell. He is very energetic and doesn't let his age slow him down. Deac is very gentle with any human he meets, whether it's an infant or an elderly individual. Deac, whenever being introduced to another dog, needs a very slow introduction. Deac comes across really aggressive at first but with a slow introduction, he will warm up to them. Whenever introducing Deac to another dog, there cannot be any other dogs around because he will become aggressive and won't be able to warm up. He needs his full attention on one dog at a time. 

   For cats, it is unknown as to whether he can be around them or not. For walks, Deac gets excited and will pull but once he gets the initial excitement out, he does really well. As stated before, he gets very excited and a little aggressive around the initial interaction around another dog that whenever he sees another dog on a walk, he will get excited and lunge towards them while barking. You'll have to pull him away and get him out of sight of the other dog. He is very treat motivated and has gotten a lot better with the lunging and barking with the walks. With a little more time and effort, he will get over that behavior. Overall, Deac is an amazing and loving dog that loves everyone. He is very young at heart and wants nothing more than for people to love him. 

Update 1/7/2021
Deac is a very loving Dane who wants nothing more than love from his humans. Deac is a 6 year old Dane who doesn't let his age get in the way. Though Deac is 6, he can still move around without any problem.  Like most Danes, Deac will get the zoomies and be his playful self. At the same time, Deac is very content with getting in his bed and laying down with his blanket. Whenever Deac goes to a new place, his energy goes up but will settle as he gets accustomed to his new home. When it comes to temperament, Deac is a very easy going dog that can read a room and adjust his energy level to match yours. Deac is very gentle and is great around people of all ages. You will not have to worry about Deac hurting small children or adults of older age. When it comes to other pets, you have to be very careful if you want to socialize Deac with other pets. 
   Deac is a very curious dog and has to have strict one on one interactions. If there are other animals running around Deac whenever you're trying to introduce him, he gets very distracted and becomes very aggressive to the other pets. If Deac can have that one on one interaction, he will warm up to the other animal. This is also the fact with going on a walk. Deac is very well behaved on a leash in terms of pulling. If there are no other dogs around, Deac is very good on leash. You'll only have to worry whenever there is another dog in sight. Deac will get very excited and start to lunge towards the other dogs and bark. Even though he does this, he has come a long way and is getting better with it, he still needs work on completely stopping this act. Deac will be adopted with a training contract to help the new adopter learn how to manage this and to teach Deac how to react better. Deac is very food motivated and tends to try and counter surf, especially if there is cake on the counter, Deac loves to try and eat cake. Deac has a skin sensitivity to some foods where his skin will turn red, getting food that is skin and stomach sensitivity friendly is perfect for him. He is the perfect dog for those who are looking for a youthful at heart dog that wants all the love and affection. If you shower him with love, he will do the same, or possibly shower you in slobber.

Dogs-case by case
Cats- No
Kids- 8+




MAGDRL only adopts to approved adopters in NY, NJ, PA MD, DE, D.C.,VA and WV. We are not able to cover full states in some cases. Please check the individual states website for more information on area coverage.

animal.description:
PLEASE NOTE! EFFECTIVE 1/1/2020.
Anyone interested in meeting or wanting more info on one of our available dogs MUST CONTACT US BY PHONE at 412 795 0163 and leave a message. NO EMAILS WILL BE ANSWERED.

The first time you meet Scooby you will say the same thing I said, "THERE IS NO WAY THIS DOG IS 12 YEARS OLD!" But it is true, his paperwork says its true. If you look at the first picture of him you will get an idea of his energy, his ears are flapping from the speed he is running toward me. He is always in motion and he craves human attemtion. Scooby came to us when his elderly owner went to assisted living. We are told Scooby was an "OUTSIDE DOG" all his life. I am not sure if that means he was chained, or if he had an outside kennel. We do know that his owner huinted with him, but again not sure if it was waterfowl or upland. Reguardless, if you are looking for an active older dog who will look at you like you are a god, this is your boy. He is healthy, vaccinated, buit is on the very thin side. Because of his weight he has not been neutered at this time.

 Please call SPARRO if you would like more info or to set up a visit with Scooby

animal.description:
Reese has recently been treated for Lyme disease and developed blindness. Reese loves a good time but she mostly loves pets and cuddles.  She's  soft, gentle and kind.  She has good manners and is ready to make someone happy.  She s a great companion .   Those aren't her puppies in the picture, she just loved them.
Age: 4 is our guess
Weight:  60 pounds 
Energy Level: sweet and adventurous 

Adoption fee: $395

Applications are at: www.rescuepups.org

Look for directions at: 
facebook.com/rescuepup585

Located in Friendship, NY approximately 90 minutes south from both Buffalo and Rochester. Rescue Pups works tirelessly to ensure that our dogs are well taken care of and they get the very best home that is a perfect match for them. While waiting to get adopted dogs are loved like family.Quality of care is the highest of our priorities. We hike daily, make sure everyone gets plenty of play time, a good quality diet and we try to do basic training. All our dogs are vaccinated, spayed or neutered, microchipped, and are given monthly advantage. The same person provides consistent quality of care.  Families who adopt from us get a well-balanced pet who trusts people. When you support us, your gift can help more dogs get adopted into loving homes. Together we can make a difference. 
Apply at Rescuepups.org

Parker loves people but due to his size and herding instincts may be best in a home with older children. A properly trained and socialized blue heeler is an excellent family dog. He is agile and tireless, loves to run and play with children and is an affectionate, fun-loving companion. He is an inside dog but loves to run outside but will dig or jump out of a fence if he is left. He needs a job or a very active family! HATES CATS.

animal.description:
Made this handsome fella named Joaquin! He came into the shelter November 9, 2020 as a stray and was never reclaimed so he is now awaiting his forever home! Joaquin is around three years old, current on shots, and excited to have a  person or family to call his own. Just a happy boy who is filled with joy and unconditional love to share. Joaquin seems to get along well with most other dogs and is super charming. Maybe you have the most perfect forever home for Joaquin? Stop by the shelter for a visit with him today in adopt him into your heart and home.
If you have another dog and are interested in meeting another potential new furry member please bring him or her to the shelter and meet on neutral ground before adopting. No need to shuffle the animals around any more than necessary. Please know that 1 mosquito bite can create heart worms and they can be fatal if not treated. It is VERY important to keep your pets healthy and protected by keeping them on a once a month heart worm and flea/tick prevention. These animals are counting on you as their owner to provide them with lots a love and the proper health care so PLEASE make sure you are aware and prepared before adopting. Owning a pet is an extra expense and responsibility but is so worth every minute and penny you invest in them. They will add lots of joy and unconditional love if given a fair chance.
The shelter is open Mon.-Fri. 10-1, 2-5 and Sat. 10-4. Adopt a homeless pet and save a life. If you can not adopt right now come out and volunteer and make a difference in the lives of these animals while they await their FOREVER home.
